{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review — T3 (Integration feasibility) on plan \"Docs: private-repo credentials, descriptive errors, ref/source semantics, HMAC trust model\":\n\nT3 is an OVERLAY that applies only when a plan integrates an external API/CLI/service/library or asserts a capability it has not used before. This plan is documentation-only — its Scope explicitly excludes code (\"Out: code (S1-S5)\"). It describes behaviors owned by the S1-S5 implementation tickets (git fetch/credential-helper requirement, ref/source semantics, HMAC trust model, REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR knobs) rather than integrating any new external capability itself. The git fetch + credential-helper/deploy-key/token mechanics are standard git, and the EFS/NFS flock caveat is already grounded in this epic's existing design note (cross-ref intact). No asserted-but-unverified external capability is introduced by the docs work.\n\nVerdict for T3: PASS (not-applicable — docs deliverable, no integration).\n\nFindings: none.\nAffirmations: T3 (integration feasibility) — not-applicable; no external API/CLI/service integration or new capability assertion in this documentation chunk."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782522340729029001,"uuid":"9deeaf34-f3f3-4bf5-aac1-dddb46678699"}